@page "/docs/focus"

<PageTitle>Focus — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / Gestures / <span>Focus</span></div>
<h1>Focus</h1>
<p>Animate an element while it has keyboard or programmatic focus. Useful for accessible interactive components.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;Motion Tag="input"
        WhileFocus="@@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.03 })"
        Transition="@@(new TransitionConfig { Type = "spring", Stiffness = 300, Damping = 20 })"
        placeholder="Click to focus" /&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo-area">
    <Motion Tag="input" Class="demo-input"
            WhileFocus="@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.04 })"
            Transition="@(new TransitionConfig { Type = TransitionType.Spring, Stiffness = 300, Damping = 20 })"
            placeholder=" Click or tab to focus" />
</div>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p><code>WhileFocus</code> uses the <code>focus</code>/<code>blur</code> events, so it responds to both mouse and keyboard navigation. This makes it ideal for highlighting focused form fields or interactive elements in a keyboard-accessible way.</p>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> Combine <code>WhileFocus</code> with <code>WhileHover</code> to create rich interactive states for buttons and form controls.
</div>
